cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.FL, cs.CG

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a likely category as the paper presents algorithms and data structures for efficiently decoding strings from their shingles. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the problem of uniquely decoding a string from its shingles is related to information theory. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper discusses time and space complexity of the proposed algorithm. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as one of the perspectives presented in the paper is an automata theoretic approach. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is less likely but still possible as the problem of string reconciliation mentioned in the paper can be seen as a geometric problem of finding overlaps between strings.
